France was the first country to recognize the constitutional right to asylum, this being enshrined in article 120 of the Constitution of 1793.[9] The modern French right of asylum is recognized by the 1958 Constitution, vis-à-vis the paragraph 4 of the preamble to the Constitution of 1946, to which the Preamble of the 1958 Constitution directly refers. The Constitution of 1946 incorporated of parts of the 1793 constitution which had guaranteed the right of asylum to "anyone persecuted because of his action for freedom" who are unable to seek protection in their home countries.

In addition to the constitutional right to asylum, the modern French right to asylum (droit d'asile) is enshrined on a legal and regulatory basis in the Code de l'Entree et du Sejour des Etrangers et du Droit d'Asile[10] (CESEDA).

France also adheres to international agreements which provide for application modalities for the right of asylum, such as the 1951 United Nations

"I used to wonder why some Palestinian people would engage in actions that could only provoke the aggressor further. Then I realized that to ask a people to live quietly, while they have no justice and no freedom, is to ask them to live "peacefully" as slaves. "Peace" without justice or freedom is slavery. It's like asking a battered woman to live "peacefully" with her abuse. We all want the bloodshed to stop. But what about the daily humiliation and institutionalized oppression?
I was reminded of a part in "The Hunger Games" when Katniss considers abandoning the resistance against the oppressor, in exchange for "safety". Gale's response was telling. He said: "Safe to do what? Starve? Work like slaves? Send their kids to the reaping?"
Consider this: If a woman is being raped, things would be a lot more "peaceful" if she didn't resist. But, asking her not to resist--just because her attacker is physically stronger--is asking her to accept her own abuse and oppression for the sake of "peace". This is what the world is asking Palestinians to do.
And sometimes what seems to the world as just ineffective tactics, like throwing a rock at a tank, is in fact an act of resistance. It is a powerful statement to the oppressor--and the world--that they refuse to be enslaved. That dignity and self-respect are even more beloved to them than their own lives.
It is a statement that you can take their lives. But not their freedom."

message: The American dentist who killed Cecil the lion is facing calls for prosecution

data.message: Lion killed my a American terrorist.

the thing is.. we should be pushing african governments to not grant licences to shoot lions. it'sawful what he did but was probably legal if he lured the lion out of a protected zone and had a permit. i don't agree with it but people are aiming at the wrong target.

I believe every murderer should face a fair trial. If it's up to me, I'd put him in a locked room with Cecil's wife and his kids(if he had). Of course after he (the dentist) cleans and sharpens their teeth..

As much as I disagree with the killing and if he is indeed guilty I want to see proper punishment, let's just get a few things straight. Firstly, he is not guilty at the moment, we here in the civilised world have the legal standing to be innocent unless proven guilty and thus far there has been no court case to prove him contrary. Secondly, the man has two children. How do you think those two children (who had NO part in the killing!) must feel to have their homes and their lives by both celebrities and ordinary civilians who want them to not have enough money to put food on the table and would gladly support 'lynch mobs'. And thirdly, do you really, honestly think that a petition will make ANY difference whatsoever? Really? The man who runs Zimbabwe has killed thousands of his own people, comited atrocious war crimes and openly threatens anyone who dares oppose him, do you really think that a petition signed by a few thousand westerners will make any bit of difference?

Don't get me wrong, I want to see justice, but only if proper and due process is followed, if not, and we 'hunt him like he hunted Cecil', how can we stand there and say we are better than he is...
Turn him over to face prosecution for the murder and mutalation of an innocent animal. Terrifying this person works in any medical field.
An American dentist ? He is so filthy greedy with human , now he dose the same thing to animals , what an animal this dentist is .

If law of the land says KILLING CECIL IS LEGAL ,  I refuse to accept but keep silent. But if law has a loophole, then ! You should understand:  'Cecil dead. Coalition weak. Pride takeover by another coalition. LIONS NEVER ADOPT. 10 cubs will be killed.'  If law permits   Make this killer dentist happy by adopting the 10 cubs, but in jail or zoo. "Love animals, the vulnerable. Love Lions, the Manly King. " - Dr Altaf

#JusticeForCecil 
  http://news.nationalgeographic.com/2015/07/150722-lions-canned-hunting-lion-bone-trade-south-africa-blood-lions-ian-michler/
So sad that the lion was killed for what a trophy to the hunters. The dentist should go to jail for killing Cecil its wrong to kill an animal or a human. Especially poaching.

Killing a Lion. Now we wish the death penalty on this man. Please. His explanation is clear and might be true. It is bad what he did. I hate hunting. In South Africa we as humans are hunted down by criminals and thousands are killed every month. Our farmers are slaughtered and butchered and suffers worst deaths than the lion did. They outcry is great about the lion. I just wish people also care so much for the thousands of people butchered in Zimbabwe and South Africa. White farmers have became the "trophies" to hunt. Children are orphaned. Let the world know we care about our animals and we hate to see our Rhino population being eradicated. The lion project is an amazing project. What happened is such a tragedy. Morever, we want protection for our farmers, farm workers and all the people who are hunted down in their houses and on their farms. Why is no one questioning why they allow government permit hunting of lions

He's guilty he killed a well loved lion, weather he new it or not it doesn't make a bit of difference , he also made the lion suffer before he made his kill, then beheaded and skinned the animal, he should have thought about his children before he did this act, if he loses everything he only has himself to blame

He needs to be prosecuted. African goverments should take responsibility for what happened too. They are corrupted. Animals are killed for sport.  And where all the charity money goes? Why after so much money poured into Africa so many children are still dying? Why people have to flee to Europe?  They are not in danger, they are poor. Until corruption is not stoped, life in Africa for people and animals will get even worse.
I actually cannot get my head around why someone would want to hurt an animal, 40 hours that poor lion suffered. Makes me sick to my stomach. Hope a lion eats him as Karma !
The lion is dead. The dentist is rich. Suggest he contribute to closely controlled wildlife reserves. Big $.
Shocking, upsetting cruelty how any 'man' thinks he's so big and brave doing this..is UTTTERLY pathetic. Pointless specimen he is to murder a majestic lion!!! DETESTABLE 'person'!!
there is a lion ( assad) in syria who kill people ..!
He should go to jail for life what he did to Cecil the lion
Put the  basted in jail for life or put him in a cage with unfed lions

Cecil was part of a lion research project run by Oxford University for the past 15 years. This trophy hunting American dentist KNEW it wasn't a legal hunt. That's why they had to lure the collared lion out of the protected reserve and onto private property by tying a dead impala to their vehicle as bait and even tried to destroy his GPS collar. (This is a common tactic used by trophy hunters to circumvent park conservation laws) Oh, and one more important thing we feel we should mention.. When the head of a pride is killed, the next male in the hierarchy will kill all of that males offspring. 24 of Cecil's cubs will also die now because of this man's selfish actions.

Why did he leave America, came to Africa only to come and kill the most popular lion in Africa? Is dat not total wickedness? Can an Africa come to USA and kill the most famous Animal there and go free? This wicked Denist should be repatriated to Africa to face the law. His hospital should be closed and his licence should be withdrawn. What did he do with Cecil's skined body? Is it Cecil that he uses in treating teeth and mouth problem? He's extremely wicked and should be killed and skined as well.
Human beings r dying daily n no one is concerned but da lion!!! Africa!

We will remember Cecil's legacy...not because he roamed free on his home soil and was protected and watched/monitored for 14 years. This precious Lion has OPENED UP THE EYES OF THE WORLD! R.I.P. CECIL. I AM SORRY YOU HAD TO ENDURE SUCH UNSPEAKABLE PAIN FOR SO LONG IN ORDER TO SHOW THE WORLD THAT THE TIME HAS COME TO ROAR FOR THE INNOCENT AND HELPLESS!

data.message: If this is a real video. This is what happens because we live in a country where are so called leaders are too busy covering their own asses and serving their own interests. Criminals nowadays have zero fear of the law because there is no semblance of leadership and it will take years to convict a Php10B thief (or it might even be swept under the rug). Ironically the biggest criminals we have are in suits and barongs in the different government agencies and that includes our irrelevant president. Us, the people who work our asses off to feed our families pay for the crimes of the people we elect in office. The President and the DILG secretary only have time for so called robberies inside  huge malls.
This is why we need someone line Mr. Duterte to be on the top ranks of our government. :(

We meet the migrants in Calais, desperately trying to reach the UK:  http://bbc.in/1DcDb2J
name: Calais migrants: One night by the fence

data.message: Why is the BBC so Focused on the "illegal immigrants" what about the poor lorry drivers and the business that are suffering
Its called 'illegal immigrants'. I am a migrant cause I did it through due process.
If they are claiming asylum then they should seek asylum in the first safe country they arrive in not trek across several to reach the UK

Stop trying to make us feel sorry for these ILLEGAL immigrants. They are not poor. As they have spent thousands to reach Calais. Notice how they're also all men also, no women. It's clear that they're coming for benefits. Deport them all now.
The UK should stop arming countries in the middle east.  That would be a good start to tackle immigration..

If death is "no worse than what [you] face in [your] country"... Why not stay in France or the first safe country you get to? Why do hordes of people like you constantly and criminally try to invade Britain?

We need to do something to stop this and deter others from trying to come!! Maybe it's time to fill in the tunnel and go back to just ferries!! Enough is enough!! If these were true asylum seekers and were so desperate then they should have registered in the first country they come not travel through 3 or 4 countries to get to the UK!!
Why risk dying to get to Britain though? Surely once they're out of their own 'dangerous' country they should settle where they land! ?

When the migrants threaten people with knives and break into lorries do we really want that in the uk? They fled their country like cowards send them back they all look like thugs . And the bbc know where they are so why don't the government do something about it?

I was born and bred here in Somalia - the country in which guns never fall silent! I have never tried to leave  Somalia despite the hardship. Sometimes I do not know where the next meal will come from but I would prefer to DIE here in my country with dignity!

I am reading about its the UK's fault it's like this. Well if everyone please look at a bloody map and look at the the United Kingdom, you can see it's fairly small compared to Eastern Europe, South Africa, Russia, Asia and much more. We have taken our fair share of immigration. We are building on our Greenland what is running out, as well as our resources, the UK is fit to burst.

Why doesn't someone ask why these people NEED to get to the UK???  I mean if they're ''fleeing'' from France it's not like they are in a third world desperate starving country no?... France is a leading economy, an EU heavyweight, part of the G8 .... UN security council .... AND has colonial ties .... so WHY the UK and not France???

I feel so sorry for these poor desperate people.  Very easy for us to judge when we do not know the horrors they have seen, the decision to leave their families, the abuse and the conditions. I feel for the lorry drivers and people affected by the problems as well.  Easy to comment when we have beds, food and no fear of death and watching from our pcs and tvs.  I don't have the answer but peoples reactions of 'don't let them into our country'  etc, astounds me, it is all our world to share.  Much more needs to be done to help, I just wish I had an answer to it all.

I don't feel sorry for these people.
